node.text:
@dragonpharma_llc
•
Want more development in your quadriceps or hamstrings? Then use this easy bodybuilding trick: Elevate your heels or toes during your next lower-body workout.

Raising your heels helps you sit deeper into your squat, which will recruit more muscle fibers and strengthen your quads. But the heels elevated squat is not an exercise for beginners. It is only to be performed by people who know how to squat properly. Practice without weight first and only when you’re comfortable with the exercise, use dumbbells or a barbell.

Check out this awesome tip from our Dragon Pharma Athlete & Coach 🐲 @kaylarossifitness!

Whether you're a gym noob or you've been pounding the weights for years we have a training tip for you. 

Be sure to turn on your notifications for more training tips from your favorite Dragon Pharma Athletes and Coaches.

Comment what other training tips you guys want to see!!! 
Repost from @dragonpharma_llc

with @kaylarossifitness 💪

What’s on the agenda for today’s workout?

"Good morning" may be an email greeting, a cute text your boo sends while away on business, or, TBH, any morning that doesn't begin with an alarm clock. But "good morning" is also an exercise you should absolutely be doing.

Good Morning Squat is one of the best ways to build leg, hip and back strength. However, this exercise is often ignored out of fear of suffering a back injury. 

Never heard of it? This video is for you. Check out this training tip of our Dragon Pharma Athlete & Coach Kayla Rossi of how to perform Good Morning Squats to get the best results!
.
Remember, there’s no excuse! Now it’s your turn to try this exercise and let us know how you like it.

Be sure to turn on your notifications for more home workouts from your favorite Dragon Pharma Athletes and Coaches.

node.text:
Full shoulder workout : 5 supersets , do 3 sets of 15 reps for each exercise in every superset . 
1. Bradford press (alternating front and back press) SUPERSET with triangle front raises 
2. Kneeling military press SUPERSET with seated lateral raises 
3. Around the worlds on preacher curl set up SUPERSET with reverse grip barbell front raises 
4. Forward leaning dumbbell presses (press out at an angle and pinch shoulder blades together) SUPERSET with reverse grip dumbbell presses 
5. Tick lateral raises (quarter , half, full is one rep) SUPERSET with upright rows 
*** FINISHER : plank step ups SUPERSET with kettle bell swings
#bouldershoulders#delts#shoulderworkout

node.text: That look when you know you about to go hard af. It’s either F*ck yes or hell no . All in or all out . I’ve never been one to do anything half way. 100% or 0% . You’ll never see me preach balance. You want balance be prepared to be mediocre . Stubborn , maybe . But it’s always going to be all or nothing for me . Live audaciously and with intent . #kaylarossifitness

node.text: Happiness is finishing an entire bowl of cereal before it gets soggy. 😍😂… no but happiness really is the little things. The small moments, the daily wins we forget to celebrate, the good people in your life. Don’t wait for things to get easier, simpler, better. Life will always be complicated. Look for small opportunities for happiness in the moment you are in right now. Im definitely guilty of this. Sometimes I get so dialed in on my goals, my vision, of where I want to be and what I want to accomplish NEXT that I forget to be grateful for everything I’ve already overcome and achieved. Instead of always being in the mindset of ok what can i do next, how can I be better, what more can I achieve, sometimes you have to live in the moment. And I’m not saying stop striving to be better or stop grinding  because you know im always going to live by that mentality, im just saying take a second to appreciate where you’ve been and how far you’ve come, then get your ass back to work! Life is pretty amazing sometimes. LIVE in that. 💎 #kaylarossifitness
